** The Sound of Silence: An Illustrated Serenade to the Art of Listening t=
o One=E2=80=99s Inner Voice Amid the Noise of Modern Life (https://www.bra=
inpickings.org/2016/09/08/the-sound-of-silence-goldsaito-kuo/?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID])
------------------------------------------------------------

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

=E2=80=9CThere are many fine things which we cannot say if we have to shou=
t=2C=E2=80=9D Henry David Thoreau observed in contemplating how silence en=
nobles speech (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/09/16/thoreau-silence-co=
nversation-walden/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) . A year earlie=
r=2C he had written in his journal (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/=
04/famous-writers-on-keeping-a-diary/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQI=
D]) : =E2=80=9CI wish to hear the silence of the night=2C for the silence=
 is something positive and to be heard.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s a sentiment=
 of almost unbearable bittersweetness today=2C a century and a half later=
=2C as we find ourselves immersed in a culture that increasingly mistakes=
 loudness for authority=2C vociferousness for voice=2C screaming for subst=
ance. We seem to have forgotten what Susan Sontag reminded us half a centu=
ry ago =E2=80=94 that =E2=80=9Csilence remains=2C inescapably=2C a form of=
 speech=2C=E2=80=9D (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/07/06/the-aestheti=
c-of-silence-susan-sontag/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) that it=
 has its own aesthetic=2C and that learning to wield it is among the great=
 arts of
living.

Of the nine kinds of silence (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/01/13/pau=
l-goodman-silence/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) that Sontag=E2=
=80=99s contemporary and friend Paul Goodman outlined=2C =E2=80=9Cthe fert=
ile silence of awareness=2C pasturing the soul=E2=80=9D is the kind we see=
m to have most hastily forsaken =E2=80=94 and yet it is also the one we mo=
st urgently need if we are to reclaim the aesthetic of silence in the art=
 of living.

That ennobling=2C endangered kind of silence is what writer Katrina Goldsa=
ito and illustrator Julia Kuo celebrate in The Sound of Silence (http://ww=
w.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&m=
c_eid=3D[UNIQID]) (public library (http://www.worldcat.org/title/sound-of=
-silence/oclc/875403891&referer=3Dbrief_results?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=
=3D[UNIQID]) ) =E2=80=94 the story of a little boy named Yoshio=2C who aw=
akens to the elusive beauty of silence amid Tokyo=E2=80=99s bustle and tea=
ches himself its secret language.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Conceptually=2C the book is a trans-temporal counterpart to In Praise of S=
hadows (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/05/28/in-praise-of-shadows-tani=
zaki/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =E2=80=94 that magnificent 1=
933 serenade to ancient Japanese aesthetics=2C lamenting how excessive ill=
umination obscures so many of life=E2=80=99s most beautiful dimensions=2C=
 just as today=E2=80=99s excessive noise silences life=E2=80=99s subtlest=
 and most beautiful signals.

Goldsaito=E2=80=99s lyrical writing=2C part ballad and part haiku=2C and K=
uo=E2=80=99s illustrations=2C midway between manga and Chris Ware (https:/=
/www.brainpickings.org/2012/11/05/building-stories-chris-ware/?mc_cid=3Dba=
245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) yet thoroughly original=2C carry the story wi=
th effortless poetic enchantment.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

We follow Yoshio as he leaves home one rainy morning and steps into the sy=
mphony of urban sounds cascading through the city =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9Craind=
rops pattering on his umbrella=2C=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cboots squishing and sq=
uashing through the puddles.=E2=80=9D

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

As he makes his way through this aural wonderland=2C he is suddenly enthra=
lled by a most magical sound. He follows it to discover a koto player tuni=
ng her instrument.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Then the koto player played. The notes were twangy and twinkling; they tic=
kled Yoshio=E2=80=99s ears! When the song finished=2C Yoshio said=2C =E2=
=80=9CSensei=2C I love sounds=2C but I=E2=80=99ve never heard a sound like=
 that!=E2=80=9D

The koto player laughed=2C and it sounded like the metal bell that swayed=
 in the wind in Mama=E2=80=99s garden.

=E2=80=9CSensei=2C=E2=80=9D Yoshio said=2C =E2=80=9Cdo you have a favorite=
 sound?=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CThe most beautiful sound=2C=E2=80=9D the koto player said=2C =E2=
=80=9Cis the sound of ma=2C of silence.=E2=80=9D

=E2=80=9CSilence?=E2=80=9D Yoshio asked. But the koto player just smiled a=
 mysterious smile and went back to playing.

Puzzled and vitalized by the cryptic message=2C the little boy sets out to=
 find the sound of silence.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

He goes to the quietest place he knows=2C the bamboo grove behind the play=
ground=2C but even there silence is ushered out by the sound of the living=
 world.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

The bamboo made a takeh-takeh-takeh sound as the wind banged its stalks to=
gether. He closed his eyes and heard the swish-swish-swish of the wind mak=
ing the leaves talk. It was beautiful=2C but it wasn=E2=80=99t silence.

As Yoshio makes his way home through the city=2C he continues to look for=
 silence =E2=80=94 at the train station=2C at the dinner table=2C in the b=
ath.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Even at night=2C while the rest of the family is sleeping=2C he listens fo=
r the silence only to hear the faint hum of a distant radio.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

The next morning=2C he arrives at school before everyone else and sits dow=
n to read a story=2C which absorbs him so wholly that he is transported to=
 the elusive place he had been searching for all along.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Suddenly=2C in the middle of a page=2C he heard it.

No sounds of footsteps=2C no people chattering=2C no radios=2C no bamboo=
=2C no kotos being tuned.

In that short moment=2C Yoshio couldn=E2=80=99t even hear the sound of his=
 own breath. Everything felt still inside him. Peaceful=2C like the garden=
 after it snowed. Like feather-stuffed futons drying in the sun.

Silence had been there all along.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

In that moment=2C he learns what we so easily forget: that silence is not=
 the absence of sound but the presence of an inward-listening awareness=2C=
 an attunement of the mind=E2=80=99s ear and an orientation of the spirit=
 toward a certain inner stillness =E2=80=94 perhaps the positive counterpo=
int to loneliness=2C which so often thrives amid the crowd (https://www.br=
ainpickings.org/2016/07/11/the-lonely-city-olivia-laing/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6=
f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) .

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

Complement the immeasurably wonderful The Sound of Silence (http://www.ama=
zon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0316203378/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=
=3D[UNIQID]) with Pablo Neruda=E2=80=99s beautiful ode to silence () and=
 John Cage on how silence helps us enlarge each other=E2=80=99s goodness (=
https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/09/15/john-cage-silence-human-nature/?m=
c_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C then revisit this manifesto for=
 silence=E2=80=99s sister virtue=2C solitude (https://www.brainpickings.or=
g/2014/09/03/how-to-be-alone-school-of-life/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D=
[UNIQID]) .


