** Dear Data: A Lyrical Illustrated Ode to How Our Attention Shapes Our Re=
ality (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/09/07/dear-data-book/?mc_cid=3Db=
a245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID])
------------------------------------------------------------

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1616895322/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

=E2=80=9CInformation is what our world runs on: the blood and the fuel=2C=
 the vital principle=2C=E2=80=9D James Gleick wrote in his indispensable h=
istory of how the age of data and human consciousness shaped one another (=
https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/09/06/james-gleick-the-information-clau=
de-shannon/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) . A generation earlier=
=2C the great theoretical physicist John Archibald Wheeler proclaimed (htt=
ps://www.brainpickings.org/2016/09/02/it-from-bit-wheeler/?mc_cid=3Dba245e=
b6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) in what remains the most resonant chorus to our a=
ge: =E2=80=9CAll things physical are information-theoretic in origin and t=
his is a participatory universe=E2=80=A6 Observer-participancy gives rise=
 to information.=E2=80=9D What we measure=2C monitor=2C record=2C and atte=
nd to is what colors our view of life. And so it is that =E2=80=9Cobserver=
-participancy=E2=80=9D has become the hallmark =E2=80=94 the chief currenc=
y=2C the focal lens =E2=80=94 of our Information Age: The quality of our a=
ttention and the nature of its recorded representation have become the inf=
ormational infrastructure of our reality.

In the spring of 2015=2C I wrote about (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015=
/03/19/dear-data-giorgia-lupi-stefanie-posavec/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=
=3D[UNIQID]) Dear Data (http://www.dear-data.com/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_=
eid=3D[UNIQID]) =E2=80=94 a wonderful project addressing this dependency=
 with uncommon lyrical elegance. In their yearlong correspondence=2C Giorg=
ia Lupi (http://giorgialupi.com/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID])=
 =2C an Italian woman living in New York=2C and Stefanie Posavec (http://w=
ww.stefanieposavec.co.uk/?mc_cid=3Dba245eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C an A=
merican woman living in London=2C chose a weekly locus of attention=2C vis=
ualized their respective data points on the back of a postcard=2C and mail=
ed these self-portraits in data across the Atlantic.

http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1616895322/braipick-20?mc_cid=3Dba2=
45eb6f0&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]

